New Records: José Ramírez was intentionally walked for a franchise-record 88th time.
Key Match Events: Lane Thomas and José Ramírez hit back-to-back eighth-inning homers.
Joey Cantillo pitched five scoreless innings.
Josh Naylor’s two-run single ignited a three-run sixth inning.
David Fry added a sacrifice fly.
Junior Caminero had a career-high three doubles for Tampa Bay.
Tampa Bay's Jose Siri's single was overturned on replay review.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cleveland has the best home record in the AL at 44-27.
The Guardians remained three games ahead of second-place Kansas City in the division.
The Rays are six back for the third AL wild card.
